   "source": [
    "# 🎬 Movie Recommender — Stage 1: Exploring the Data\n",
    "\n",
    "Before building *any* model, a good data scientist **looks at the data first**.\n",
    "This is called **Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)**. We want to answer:\n",
    "\n",
    "- What does each file contain?\n",
    "- How are ratings distributed? (Do people mostly give high scores?)\n",
    "- How active are users, and how popular are movies?\n",
    "- How *sparse* is the data? (This shapes which models work.)\n",
    "\n",
    "> **Before running this**, make sure you've downloaded the data — see the\n",
    "> project README's \"Get the data\" section. The cells below expect\n",
    "> `movies.csv` and `ratings.csv` in `../data/raw/`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Setup\n",
    "\n",
    "We import the libraries we'll use and tell pandas where the data lives.\n",
    "`pandas` is the workhorse for tabular data; `matplotlib`/`seaborn` make charts."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Looking for data in: /Users/songshuqi/Documents/Machine_Learning/projects/01-movie-recommender/data/raw\n",
      "Files found: ['links.csv', 'tags.csv', 'ratings.csv', 'movies.csv']\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "\n",
    "sns.set_theme(style=\"whitegrid\")  # nicer default chart style\n",
    "\n",
    "# Path to the raw data, relative to this notebook (notebooks/ -> ../data/raw)\n",
    "RAW = Path(\"..\") / \"data\" / \"raw\"\n",
    "print(\"Looking for data in:\", RAW.resolve())\n",
    "print(\"Files found:\", [p.name for p in RAW.glob(\"*.csv\")])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Load the data\n",
    "\n",
    "MovieLens splits its data across files. The two we care about most:\n",
    "\n",
    "- **`movies.csv`** — one row per movie: `movieId`, `title`, `genres`.\n",
    "- **`ratings.csv`** — one row per rating: `userId`, `movieId`, `rating`, `timestamp`.\n",
    "\n",
    "The `ratings` table is the heart of a recommender: it records *who liked what*."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
